Trading notions of scale, the
way we build and the way we

00:36:19.600 --> 00:36:20.600
organize our cities.

00:36:20.600 --> 00:36:23.900
And we believe that this next
thing, the connected entities

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:29.040
that cars are, will change
that yet once again.

00:36:29.040 --> 00:36:32.150
And cars-- it's
interesting, because when

00:36:32.150 --> 00:36:35.810
we look at 10 years ago, cars
were really super optimized.

00:36:35.810 --> 00:36:38.220
They had the engine optimized
and all this other stuff.

00:36:38.220 --> 00:36:40.780
But as people are using
phones in different ways

00:36:40.780 --> 00:36:43.350
and people are using
connectivity in different ways,

00:36:43.350 --> 00:36:45.580
they have, as Greg
pointed out, expectations

00:36:45.580 --> 00:36:47.880
of how they can also
use this in the car

00:36:47.880 --> 00:36:50.060
as they're spending more
and more time in the car.

00:36:50.060 --> 00:36:53.400
And so this is very clear that
this is a brand-new platform.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:58.230
And we think about computing
in a very different way.

00:36:58.230 --> 00:37:02.610
And so as we think about this,
it's become very clear to us

00:37:02.610 --> 00:37:07.630
that cars, connected cars, do
become a thing unto themselves.

00:37:07.630 --> 00:37:10.830
In the past, when mobile
phones first came out,

00:37:10.830 --> 00:37:13.240
people tried to shoehorn the
PC interfaces into mobile

00:37:13.240 --> 00:37:14.580
by just shrinking it.

00:37:14.580 --> 00:37:15.660
It was a bad idea.

00:37:15.660 --> 00:37:19.510
So the phone has come a long way
to develop its own interface.

00:37:19.510 --> 00:37:22.850
And real change will
happen to the car UIs.

00:37:22.850 --> 00:37:24.530
They're not just
smartphone interfaces

00:37:24.530 --> 00:37:26.240
that are a little bit
blown up, but they

00:37:26.240 --> 00:37:29.640
will happen as cars become
their own connected thing

00:37:29.640 --> 00:37:32.350
in themselves.

00:37:32.350 --> 00:37:35.990
And so we're almost at
the end of this talk.

00:37:35.990 --> 00:37:39.810
And if you remember only
two things from this talk,

00:37:39.810 --> 00:37:41.610
we want you to take away this.

00:37:41.610 --> 00:37:45.640
First thing is, we really
learn that we needed

00:37:45.640 --> 00:37:47.350
a completely different
model for the UI

00:37:47.350 --> 00:37:52.080
to get design for
driving optimized.

00:37:52.080 --> 00:37:55.140
And the second thing
is that Android

00:37:55.140 --> 00:37:58.700
as an operating system, and
specifically Android Auto,

00:37:58.700 --> 00:38:02.730
helps you with building
some of this expertise

00:38:02.730 --> 00:38:04.620
directly into the
building blocks you get

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:06.180
to use for making applications.

00:38:06.180 --> 00:38:07.660
And this is a long process.

00:38:07.660 --> 00:38:11.120
Because of all the safety and
driver destruction implication,

00:38:11.120 --> 00:38:13.390
we have to very thoroughly
test all this stuff.

00:38:13.390 --> 00:38:16.520
But the future is very exciting.

00:38:16.520 --> 00:38:18.770
We as an operating
system are also

00:38:18.770 --> 00:38:21.590
starting to learn to
almost morph and adapt

00:38:21.590 --> 00:38:24.740
the UI to new constraints and
to future form factors that we

00:38:24.740 --> 00:38:25.974
haven't even thought about.

00:38:25.974 --> 00:38:27.640
And believe me, there's
some crazy stuff

00:38:27.640 --> 00:38:29.098
out there that we
see at auto shows

00:38:29.098 --> 00:38:31.690
where the screen's
like hugely wide.

00:38:31.690 --> 00:38:34.340
And normal computing
environment,

00:38:34.340 --> 00:38:37.550
normal adaptive responsive
design doesn't even follow this

00:38:37.550 --> 00:38:39.590
and wouldn't have
a response to that.

00:38:39.590 --> 00:38:42.240
So we're only at the
beginning of this evolution.

00:38:42.240 --> 00:38:44.380
And we see this as
the starting point.

00:38:44.380 --> 00:38:48.590
And we can wait to see what
together, you and us, will

00:38:48.590 --> 00:38:50.739
build from this going forward.

00:38:50.739 --> 00:38:52.030
Thank you very much for coming.

00:38:52.030 --> 00:38:53.610
GREG NEISWANDER: Thank you.

